title: Mokugyo (Gong) with Dragon Heads
provenance: Collection of Carol B. Brener and Stephen W. Brener
description: In the form of a mokugyo, or gong, with two dragon heads at top, both joined by single pearl clasped in their mouths. Identical on front and back. Dragon heads form lid, hinged on side. Reserve on box body with scales likely intended as striker.
